message.entry: Number of elements in INPUTSIG must be an integer multiple of EQOBJ.nSampPerSym.
TRAINSIG must be numeric vector, with length less than or equal to length(INPUTSIG)/EQOBJ.nSampPerSym.
Training signal is ignored for constant modulus algorithm.
TRAINSIG will be truncated to a length equal to length(INPUTSIG)- delay, where delay = (EQOBJ.RefTap-1)/EQOBJ.nSampPerSym.
Signal constellation with non-constant magnitude may cause CMA equalizer to be unstable.
Equalizer unstable. Try adjusting step size or forgetting factor.
SigConst must be a row vector with 2 or more elements.
To equalize a signal X, use Y=EQUALIZE(EQOBJ, X) where EQOBJ is an equalizer object.\nFor more information, type ''help equalize'' in MATLAB
